-- IDC Plans to Invest $1.7 Billion in Environmentally Friendly Developments
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-09-22T06:31:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/idc-plans-to-invest-1-7-billion-in-environmentally-friendly-developments.html
South Africa’s Industrial
Development Corp. plans to invest 11.7 billion rand in
“environmentally friendly” development projects over the next
“few” years, Economic Development Minister Ebrahim Patel said.  The IDC has started a Green Economy Fund, Patel said at a
function before the start of the third day of the ruling African  National Congress’ National General Council in Durban today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
